Requirements:
  Minotor uses RtMidi¹, it have been developped using 1.0.15².
  Minotor could be used with the RtMidi backend you want but have been tested and developped with ALSA support only.

  Under Debian and derivated, RtMidi package could not be used as well: you need to patch it this way:

$ cd /tmp
$ apt-get source rtmidi
$ cd rtmidi-1.0.15~ds0/
$ nano debian/rules
Here, change this line:
  CONFIGURE_FLAGS = --with-jack
into
  CONFIGURE_FLAGS = 
Save the file, then exit editor.
$ dpkg-buildpackage -b
$ sudo dpkg -i ../librtmidi*.deb

[1] http://www.music.mcgill.ca/~gary/rtmidi/
[2] http://www.music.mcgill.ca/~gary/rtmidi/release/rtmidi-1.0.15.tar.gz

 from Debian/Ubuntu repository
